 ```
+
+## Predicates
+
+`createPredicate` filters entities by trait values. Its dependencies must be data-bearing
+traits (not tags or relations), and their data is supplied to the callback in dependency order.
+Predicates are filters only, so they do not add values to `readEach` or `updateEach` tuples.
+
+```ts
+import { createPredicate } from 'koota'
+
+const IsHealthy = createPredicate([Health], ([health]) => health.current > 0)
+
+world.query(IsHealthy)
+world.query(Not(IsHealthy)) // Includes entities without Health
+world.query(Or(IsHealthy, IsBoss))
+```
+
+Predicate filters re-evaluate when a dependency is added or set. They can also be used with
+tracking modifiers: `Added(IsHealthy)` reports false-to-true transitions, `Removed(IsHealthy)`
+reports true-to-false transitions, and `Changed(IsHealthy)` reports either transition.
